         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">16/2/79 ¶ I write a few lines to you, dear Dr Beccari, assuming that by this time you have quietly settled down at your post in Florence, and altho' you will not rest on your " ¶ laurels ¶ ", you will...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">79.02.16</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To Odoardo Beccari</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">University of Florence, Science Library: Botany, Archives, Beccari 12/32</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">16/2/79</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">I write a few lines to you, dear Dr Beccari, assuming that by this time you have quietly settled down at your post in Florence, and altho' you will not rest on your "<seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">laurels</hi>
               </seg>", you will doubtless now — after having faced so many dangers and earned so much "glory" — proceed to publish regularly your researches, and enjoy the quietness of settled literary life with — I hope — a happy household. </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I look forward with much interest to the continuation of your important "Malesia".<note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Beccari (1877-90).</p>
               </note> Recently I have reviewed a small collection of plants from Mr Goldie and several other collections from the missionary The Reverend J. Chalmers. The specimens are mostly too imperfect for accurate examination, still I may manage to publish on them 16 pages more (No VI) of the Papuan plants.<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Part VI of Papuan plants, B85.06.03, was not published for some time, and contained no plants contributed by Goldie.</p>
               </note> The species, which I recognize are nearly all known, only about 3 or 4 new ones; and as your Papuan collections came all from the N. W. and those obtained for me are all from the S. E., it is not likely that we shall clash in any <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">minor</hi>
               </seg> publication of mine.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Your Sumatra &amp; Borneo collections must also be teaming<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>teeming?</p>
               </note> with so much novelty that you can well afford to leave a few novelties to me. Kindly consider, that unless I can go on with the "Papuan plants", I shall have nothing to <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">encourage</hi>
               </seg> the Missionaries to continue their sendings to me. Among the plants recently received from New Guinea are spec of the following genera not yet mentioned in my "Papuan plants": <name key="Oxalis">Oxalis</name>, <name key="Mollinedia">Mollinedia</name>
               <name key="Aristotelia">Aristotelia</name>
               <name key="Gomphrena">Gomphrena</name>, <name key="Coccoloba">Coccoloba</name>, <name key="Alphitonia">Alphitonia</name>, <name key="Elatostemma">Elatostemma</name>, <name key="Carumbium">Carumbium</name>, <name key="Chloranthus">Chloranthus</name>, <name key="Nauclea">Nauclea</name>, Eryth[rinia]<note xml:id="ftn4" type="footnote" n="4">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>uncertain transcription: interlined.</p>
               </note>
               <name key="Vittadinia">Vittadinia</name>
               <name key="Centipeda">Centipeda</name>, <name key="Dichrocephala">Dichrocephala</name>, <name key="Crepis">Crepis</name>, Eranthemum, <name key="Physalis">Physalis</name>, Diospyros, <name key="Coleus">Coleus</name>, <name key="Spathoglottis">Spathoglottis</name>, <name key="Dianella">Dianella</name>, <name key="Tacca">Tacca</name>, <name key="Smilax">Smilax</name>, <name key="Aneilema">Aneilema</name>, <name key="Habenaria">Habenaria</name>, <name key="Pennisetum">Pennisetum</name>, <name key="Sporobolus">Sporobolus</name>, <name key="Chionachne">Chionachne</name>, <name key="Isachne">Isachne</name>, <name key="Ophioglossum">Ophioglossum</name>, &amp;c, (the <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">sp.</hi>
               </seg> nearly all well known).</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>You will be <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">sad </hi>
               </seg>to learn, that our generous friend, Chev. Marinucci, died suddenly last month from intestinal inflammation.<note xml:id="ftn5" type="footnote" n="5">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The Italian Consul-General to Australia died on 6 February 1879 (<seg style="font-style: italic; ">Argus</seg>, 7 February 1879, p. 5, col. a)</p>
               </note> What a kind and excellent man he was, particularly attached to myself. I shall miss him very much indeed, and the Italian Government will find it difficult to obtain so excellent a Representative again.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">With regardful remembrance your</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. von Mueller.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>When you send me any N. Guin, plants, then please send the <name key="Leguminosae">Leguminosae</name> first.<note xml:id="ftn6" type="footnote" n="6">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Marginal note, p. 1.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Dr Scheffer sent a large lot of <name key="Rubiaceae">Rubiaceae</name> of Dutch India, but they [are] all described in Miquels volumes.<note xml:id="ftn7" type="footnote" n="7">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Marginal note, p. 2. Miquel (1855-9)?</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>My best salutation to Dr Giglioli.<note xml:id="ftn8" type="footnote" n="8">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Marginal note, p. 3.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
